        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Metroid Prime 4: Beyond "Out Now" Poster Spotted In London]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gamespot.com/articles/metroid-prime-4-beyond-out-now-poster-spotted-in-london/1100-6532578/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/metroid-prime-4-beyond-out-now-poster-spotted-in-london.1223763/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://www.gamespot.com/articles/metroid-prime-4-beyond-out-now-poster-spotted-in-london/1100-6532578/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><p>
    <span data-nosnippet="">GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links.</span>
  </p><article itemscope="" data-type-id="1100" data-guid="1100-6532578">

            
            
  


        

  


        
        
              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>Gamers have been waiting 18 years for <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/metroid-prime-4-everything-we-know/1100-6492292/" data-ref-id="1100-6492292">Metroid Prime 4: Beyond</a> to arrive, so it was understandable when Nintendo reiterated that <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/yes-metroid-prime-4-is-still-coming-out-in-2025/1100-6529216/" data-ref-id="1100-6529216">the game will be released this year</a> to assuage fears of any further delays. While the game still doesn't have an official release date, there are now ads in the London Underground that state Metroid Prime 4: Beyond is "out now." [<strong>Update: </strong>As expected, Nintendo confirmed the ad is "incorrect" in a statement shared with <a href="https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/metroid-prime-4-beyond-ad-on-london-underground-wrongly-claims-the-game-is-out-now/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">VGC</a>.]</p><p>A picture of the ad was posted on <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/gaming/comments/1lfoblm/metroid_prime_4_beyond_out_now_advert_spotted_in/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Reddit</a>, where it's become the topic of speculation. But don't get too excited. It's far more likely that this is a mistake rather than Nintendo shadow dropping one of its most-anticipated titles of the year in the wake of Switch 2's launch without a proper media push.</p>



    
